festival.introText:
For one weekend a year, the gorgeous Peak District countryside becomes home to the Y Not Festival.

There has been steady, organic growth since it began life as a gathering of young people attending an overspilling house party in deepest, darkest, Derbyshirest, Derbyshire. But it does retain the carefree, good-time atmosphere of those original, dawning years.

The festival is still run by the same small team of passionate enthusiasts it was all those years ago (albeit a little older and a little wiser), but with the same ethos at heart – great people having a great time makes a great festival.

Stunning panoramic views of the countryside, a fully stocked bar of local ales and ciders, a mouth-watering selection of food and more live music than you could ever possibly take in.

All you need to provide is the memories (and a killer fancy dress outfit).

faqs.question: When is Y Not Festival 2023?
faqs.answer: Y Not Festival takes place on Friday 28th July - Sunday 30th July 2023.

faqs.question: How do I get to Y Not Festival by car?
faqs.answer:
If you're driving to Y Not Festival and planning to park then you will need a car park pass. These are cheapest when purchased in advance (£20).

 

The address is Pikehall, Derbyshire, DE4 2PG.

faqs.question: How do I get to Y Not Festival by car?
faqs.answer:
If you're driving to Y Not Festival and planning to park then you will need a car park pass. These are cheapest when purchased in advance (20) and will cover you for the whole weekend.

The address is Pikehall, Derbyshire, DE4 2PG.

faqs.question: Does Y Not Festival have on-site camping?
faqs.answer: Yes, all tickets for Y Not Festival include Weekend Camping. Glamping or Campervan tickets can be bought seperately.

faqs.question: Do I have to buy a ticket for a child?
faqs.answer: Children aged 12 and under are allowed into Y Not Festival for free, but you will need to book this in advance. If you show up on the day without tickets, you will be turned away.

faqs.question: Where is Y Not Festival?
faqs.answer: Y Not Festival is located at Pikehall, Derbyshire DE5 2PG.

faqs.question: How do I get to Y Not Festival by public transport?
faqs.answer:
The nearest railway stations are:

  • Buxton - approx. 20 mins away by car/bus
  • Matlock (NOT Matlock Bath) - approx. 17 mins away by car/bus

faqs.question: Can I visit my friends in family camping?
faqs.answer: You need a family wristband to enter the family camping area. These are available at no extra cost, just specify when purchasing your festival tickets. If you have already bought tickets and require a wristband, you will need to email customerservices@gigantic.com in advance - you will not be able to change ticket type at the festival itself.

faqs.question: Can I leave and re-enter Y Not Festival?
faqs.answer: Yes, but you may only bring in alcohol on your first entry to the campsite. You will need to show your wristband each time you re-enter.

faqs.question: How much alcohol can I bring to Y Not Festival?
faqs.answer: You can bring alcohol to the campsite only, and only when you first enter. Glass will not be permitted and will be confiscated upon entry.

faqs.question: Are there any age restrictions at Y Not Festival?
